<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8883> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8883" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 727" ;
	dprr:hasID 8883 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7302> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7302" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 212. According to Livy (26.29.10) he was sent with Scipio to Spain as propraetor, but on the strength of the phrase eodem lure eodem imperio mecum, i.e., with Scipio (Liv. 28.28.14), both Jashemski, Procon. And Propr. Imperium 25-26, and Sumner, Arethusa 3, 1970, 85-88, rightly hold that he was sent in 210 with imperium pro consule like Scipio himself (cf. MRR 1.280). See above, on C. Claudius Nero (246), Cos. 207.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7302 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1753> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1753" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued in command, probably pro praetore, under Scipio, and took part in the battle of Ilipa and other operations, and held command at New Carthage while Scipio visited Syphax in Africa (Polyb. 11.20, 23.1, 26.6; Liv. 28.13.3-5, 14.15-16, 16.9-12 and 15, 17.11, 26.7, 34.12,{300} cf. 28.14; App. Ib. 26, 28, 32). According to Polyb. 11.33.8 Scipio left Silanus and Marcius (see Legates) in command when he returned, but Liv. names Cornelius Lentulus and Manlius Acidinus (28.38.1)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1753 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1725> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1725" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued in command with Scipio in Spain, where he defeated Hanno and Mago among the Celtiberians (Liv. 28.1.4-2.14; Zon. 9.8; see above, on Scipio)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1725 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1719> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1719" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy omits the regular list of prorogations for this year with the exception of Q. Fulvius Flaccus." ;
	dprr:hasID 1719 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1691> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1691" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Spain along with Scipio (Liv. 27.22.7; see above, on Scipio)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1691 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1659> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1659" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued, probably as Propraetor (see 210), until the Senate should recall him (Liv. 27.7.17). Remained in charge of the forces at the base south of the Ebro while Scipio took New Carthage (Liv. 26.42.1, cf. 49.4; Polyb. 10.6.7; see above, on Scipio)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1659 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1619> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1619" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Accompanied Scipio to Spain as Propraetor (Liv. 26.19.10; cf. 28.28.14) where he succeeded to the command of Nero's army (26.19-20; Zon. 9.7; cf. Polyb. 10.6.7)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1619 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1618> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1618" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In a speech of Scipio Livy (28.28.14) says of Silanus \"eodem iure eodem imperio... missus,\" and Polybius (10.6.7) refers to him as {Gr}. See Jashemski (25f.), who may be right in holding that the Propraetor was sent to Spain with an imperium pro consule." ;
	dprr:hasID 1618 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1567> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1567" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Etruria (Liv. 26.1.5). See 210, Promagistrates." ;
	dprr:hasID 1567 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1519> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1519" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent grain from Etruria to the armies besieging Capua (Liv. 25.20. 1-3, cf. 22.5)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1519 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1395> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1395" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In charge of the garrison at Naples (Liv. 23.15.2; see Weissenborn on this passage and on 27.12.4)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1395 .
